The physicist's professional career models and their prerequisites are discussed. The theoretical basis of general demands for teaching and public performance are introduced. Reports and team work are used as the methods of teaching.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to introduce the MSc students with striking examples to the models of physicist's professional career, prerequisites needed for realizing them and strategies of professional success. As well as to practice various techniques for planning and self-analysis. Another goal is to develop the public communication skills of the students and abilities to describe their own professional work and the importance of it to different level audiences.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course, the student is expected to be able to: 1. Describe the models of physicist's professional career and prerequisites needed to realize them. 2. Describe the success strategy relevant to the personally preferred career model and the related problems. 3. Implement self-analysis by assessing own strengths and aspects requiring development in planning the professional career. 4. Recognise time planning techniques and implement them when prioritizing and adjusting activities. 5. Give information related to own profession by taking into account audience's former knowledge and specificity and by using appropriate engagement and visualization methods.  6. Formulate questions to hold professional conversation, answer questions competently and give constructive criticism.  7. Create a CV, a letter of motivation and a reference letter when applying for a job, and have an understanding of participation in individual and group interviews.
